      <h2>Our Values</h2>
      <ul>
      <li><strong>Creativity and fun ● </strong>We embody a creative, playful, welcoming environment.</li>
      <li><strong>Professionalism & the Highest Quality Coders ● </strong>We are competent hard-working professionals who value a healthy work-life balance. Our instructors are experienced senior developers with a wide range of skills, knowledge of current technologies, and passion for teaching. We hold ourselves and our students to the highest standards, insisting on nothing less than excellence.</li>
      <li><strong>Equity and Opportunity ● </strong>We firmly believe in equity of access and strive to provide opportunity and support to women and others who have experienced disadvantage in this industry.</li>
      <li><strong>Community ●</strong>  We depend on our community for support and we are deeply committed to always repaying the communities we draw from. We understand that some of the most valuable learning happens in communities. We are dedicated to fostering supportive, engaged, welcoming and safe communities in the virtual and the physical world.</li>
      <li><strong>Collaborative ● </strong>  We value collaboration over competition; when our partners and peers are stronger, everyone is stronger.
      <li><strong>Real-World, Hands-on, Experiential Education ● </strong> We believe education should be inspiring and exciting but also practical and based on real-world marketable skills. We teach students using Agile methodologies and emphasize the importance of using the right tools for the job and understanding the value and strengths of different languages and technologies. </li>
      <li><strong>Flexible and Adaptable ● </strong>Because the world of web development is a constantly evolving field, we place the highest priority on paying attention to the job market and the skills our partner employers are seeking to ensure the success of our graduates. </li>
      <li><strong>Living Wages & Employment for Oregon ●</strong>We live in a global economy but our heart is in Oregon and our intention is to support the creation of jobs in Oregon by empowering Oregonians (recent and long-time residents alike) to be the most skillful, most bad-ass programmers around with great careers that pay living wages in a growing industry.</li>
      </ul>

